reviews.subject: Introduction to Psychology
reviews.review: Dr. Smith is an excellent professor who explains concepts clearly and is always willing to help students.

reviews.subject: Calculus I
reviews.review: The lectures are detailed, but the exams are quite challenging. Extra study is required.

reviews.subject: Modern European History
reviews.review: Very engaging lectures, but the reading load is heavy. Still, she makes history interesting.

reviews.subject: Organic Chemistry
reviews.review: Content is difficult, and the lectures are fast-paced. Not very approachable outside of class.

reviews.subject: Introduction to Sociology
reviews.review: Dr. Davis is amazing! Her passion for sociology is contagious, and she really cares about her students.

reviews.subject: Macroeconomics
reviews.review: The course is solid, but Professor Wilson's teaching style is a bit dry. You need to be self-motivated.

reviews.subject: Spanish Literature
reviews.review: Dr. Gonzalez is very knowledgeable and creates a welcoming environment for discussions.

reviews.subject: Introduction to Computer Science
reviews.review: Professor Chen is a fantastic teacher. His explanations are clear, and he's always available for help.

reviews.subject: Physics II
reviews.review: Difficult material, and Dr. Johnson's lectures are hard to follow. Study sessions are a must.

reviews.subject: World Literature
reviews.review: Great discussions and a diverse selection of texts. Professor Clark encourages critical thinking.

reviews.subject: Statistics for Social Sciences
reviews.review: Dr. Martinez is knowledgeable, but the lectures can be monotonous. The material is useful, though.

reviews.subject: Biology I
reviews.review: Professor White is an incredible lecturer who makes complex topics accessible and interesting.

reviews.subject: Political Science 101
reviews.review: Engaging lectures with real-world examples. Dr. Harris is very approachable for extra help.

reviews.subject: Introduction to Philosophy
reviews.review: The lectures are abstract and hard to follow. Professor Lewis can be unresponsive to questions.

reviews.subject: Environmental Science
reviews.review: Dr. Walker is passionate about the subject and provides lots of real-world examples.

reviews.subject: Art History
reviews.review: Fantastic course! Professor Perez's enthusiasm for art is evident in every lecture.

reviews.subject: Microeconomics
reviews.review: Challenging course with a lot of math. Dr. Thomas is knowledgeable but not very engaging.

reviews.subject: Creative Writing
reviews.review: Professor King is inspiring and gives constructive feedback on assignments.

reviews.subject: Introduction to Anthropology
reviews.review: Dr. Moore is an outstanding professor who makes every lecture interesting and relatable.

reviews.subject: Chemistry I
reviews.review: The material is tough, and Professor Turner's lectures are not very clear. Be prepared to study hard.
